Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.62,0:01:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On March 16th, 1945, the fall of Iwo Jima created a foothold for the invasion of mainland Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.32,0:01:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to further strengthen their invasion plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.33,0:01:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Commander-in-Chief of the United States Fifth Fleet, General Spruance, was put in charge of this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.80,0:02:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,An order to capture Okinawa was issued.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.68,0:02:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Under his command was Lieutenant General Mitscher's high-speed aircraft carrier unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.86,0:02:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and a fleet led by a major general with 10 battleships, 9 heavy cruisers, and 23 destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, under his command is a large unit of 1,317 ships, 1,727 carrier-based aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.94,0:02:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and 452,000 personnel, including a fleet led by Rawlings a Vice Admiral of the Royal Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.28,0:02:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, the Japanese Combined Fleet Command was only the battleship Yamato, a few light cruisers, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.20,0:02:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.52,0:02:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was all that remained of the Japanese Navy's proud combined fleet since Marshal Togo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.40,0:03:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The End of the Coalition Fleet (Episode 24)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.26,0:03:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the US began landings on Okinawa on April 1st, at 4:06 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command of Vice Admiral Buckner of the 10th Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey it’s ridiculously quiet. Isn't there a Japanese army? {Not sure if what he says before the scene changes is a word or just a noise}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.47,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strange. I thought that they would fight on the beaches since the Japanese army is so good at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.82,0:03:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Commander-in-Chief of the garrison, Lieutenant General Ushijima, was determined to carry out a defense in depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.56,0:03:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was waiting for the US military to move southward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.96,0:04:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Combined Fleet Command, which was angry with this passive approach,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,issued a dispatch order to the second fleet under Yamato, who had been waiting off the coast of Mitajiri.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.78,0:04:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On April 6th, a strategy meeting for this sortie order was held on the Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.62,0:04:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially on this day, Chief of Staff Soka and Chief of Staff Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.26,0:04:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Combined Fleet Command attended for encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.37,0:04:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Secretary has just explained, we will load enough fuel to go one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but I would like you to look at the documents you have regarding this strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question before starting the strategy meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Staff Officer Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.86,0:04:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question from the Combined Fleet Command today,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I would like to ask you about what command intends to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:04:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.64,0:05:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.92,0:05:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we are not dissatisfied with the special attack order itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.97,0:05:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the purpose of this order is unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.08,0:05:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The order says to destroy enemy ships around Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.21,0:05:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, can you achieve that purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.96,0:05:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be eight days to one week after the enemy landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.49,0:05:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Their air base will have been improved and the enemy air corps readied. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.10,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The US military will have a considerable numerical advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.28,0:05:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We also estimate there to be 10 aircraft carriers nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,While the enemy is waiting, we are setting our time and course and rushing into their trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight days is too little to be a decoy, We must attract the enemies here to squeeze the forces on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Only we will drown in this special attack, not headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this just an idea from headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.44,0:06:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand well. Maybe that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There was considerable disagreement within the Combined Fleet Command
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.92,0:06:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about how Ito and Yamato are to be used now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuel for only one way, no support aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.93,0:06:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it is boasted as an unsinkable battleship this is still a messy strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.12,0:06:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, while understanding that, I want you to understand the circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.47,0:06:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,under which such a strategy must be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to have a drink after such a long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okinawa is the biggest game. Losing Okinawa now is the same as deciding Japan's fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't win unless 100 million sacrifice themselves in a suicidal attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be various theories,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.90,0:06:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, we are just the forerunners of this 100 million suicidal attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Commander-in-Chief of the combined Fleet, Toyoda, asked me to let Yamato's flowers bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want the flowers to bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are alive, do you go to eat Togakushi soba again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.46,0:07:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.10,0:07:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need something, I could visit from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Its been cleaned up. It has a nice face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.85,0:07:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you smoked at all these last few days?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I smoke about 100 a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ration alone is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.70,0:07:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.26,0:07:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.06,0:07:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was my decision to undertake this special attack wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.60,0:08:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.90,0:08:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that your family also volunteered for the kamikaze unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.16,0:08:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is another purpose behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, as you say, we may be sunk on the way. But, I want to go to the coast of Okinawa and sink ourselves there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, I want to make us a floating battery and fire the world's largest 46 cm cannons again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.18,0:08:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I also thought about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get there somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.42,0:08:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.38,0:08:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Second Fleet set out with a secret decision in response to HQ's idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Befitting a sortie that would remain in the records for a long time, Chief Ito's instruction was signaled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God's body, now is the time to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The prosperity of the empire depends on this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:09:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Struggle with each other, destroy all your enemies, and show your true potential as kamikaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.18,0:09:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he passed the Bungo Channel, Yamato had already been spotted by an enemy submarine,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.29,0:09:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was something that reminded him of the difficulties ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:10:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Around that time, General Spruance, Commander-in-Chief of the Okinawa Landing Corps,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.14,0:10:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was attacked by 400 Japanese Special Attack Units that took off from Kanoya and other bases.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.99,0:10:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was overwhelmed by his obligations and command, and had a late dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to interrupt you during your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Davis, what do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have just finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.95,0:10:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a terrible day. Who knew there were such airplanes still in Japan. {Not sure if "We had a terrible day is Davis's line or not. It is not quite clear from HA's subs}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kamikaze planes are a gift of Tokyo Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.46,0:10:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the damage caused by the special attack aircraft was 3 destroyers, 1 LST,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.58,0:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and 2 ammunition ships sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.42,0:10:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with the destruction of the light aircraft carrier San Jacinto, 15 destroyers, and 4 minesweepers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.33,0:11:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to the turmoil, battleship North Carolina, light cruiser Burnett, two transport ships, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,one LST were damaged by friendly fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One transport ship was also damaged in a collision.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There is news that will make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.92,0:11:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lover will make an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato ts finally coming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.52,0:11:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a report from the submarine Threadfin. {Name checks out https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Threadfin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.62,0:11:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Now that's a lover. How do I welcome her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.00,0:11:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the operation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the only report on the Japanese fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.75,0:11:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, there are two facts that can be drawn from this report.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One is when Yamato comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The other is that the enemy forces are weak with just about 10 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.71,0:11:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.88,0:11:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Davis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.90,0:11:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We will have one choice and one question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.73,0:11:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, how do we defeat Yamato?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.55,0:12:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The other question is where will Yamato go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand the question of where Yamato will go, but how will we defeat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Musashi and Prince of Wales, by flooding them with aircraft or with a decisive fleet battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Naval battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.26,0:12:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,According to this information, the enemy is naked with no air cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.16,0:12:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Yamato has the largest cannons in the world when it comes to naval battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.94,0:12:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the Prince of Wales was sunk by airplane, a decisive fleet battle without airplanes is unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.52,0:12:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, Spruance decided to fight with the old-fashioned surface fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.30,0:12:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why make that decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.85,0:13:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,General Spruance's decision to engage in a naval battle as a way to meet Yamato was communicated to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.09,0:13:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General of the Attack Support Unit and Lieutenant General Mitscher of the carrier fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.97,0:13:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's stupid. The main force of the Navy is now the aircraft carrier unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.24,0:13:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, since we are going to fight a naval battle, should the air force be responsible for only a light jab?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He has gotten too old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.26,0:13:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The honor of defeating Yamato, the embodiment of the Japanese Navy, is naturally decided to be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the aircraft carrier unit, which is representative of the US Navy, and our 58 MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.70,0:13:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any other way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, General Spruance is allowing us to make a jab.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.30,0:13:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it is not an uppercut, if you do it quickly, you can bring down the opponent with just a jab.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I understand. I will tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,From the Major General, it seems that everyone is celebrating and going up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They thanked you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.48,0:14:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was happy, it’s only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.21,0:14:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Battleships should fight battleships.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.18,0:14:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you support the landing party, if you hit only on land, our skills will dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.64,0:14:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,38 years ago, when I graduated from the Annapolis Naval Academy and was in Japan on a diplomatic trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was with Admiral Togo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just me, we were all Navy soldiers, they were longing to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,While there we learned Togo's strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Japanese sumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.40,0:14:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The naked fighters?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It is said that defeating the senior who taught them is to "Return the favor".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.31,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the senior congratulates the juniors who beat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.42,0:14:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.91,0:14:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do this now. I want to give back to the respectable Japanese fleets raised by Togo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato was proceeding on a peaceful voyage without knowing that General Spruance 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.35,0:15:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,was waiting to meet him based on such a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds are thick today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.74,0:15:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If they keep going like this, it will be much harder for the enemy to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.86,0:15:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy aircraft spotted! {feels like some missing lines in here}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-aircraft combat, man your stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy spotted. 31 degrees 22 minutes north latitude 129 degrees 14 minutes east longitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:16:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato-class battleship one or two, 8 destroyers, course 300, speed 12 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a full-scale air raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does Yamato go if their course is 300?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Its not Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it Sasebo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let it escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.50,0:16:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you catch up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We can catch up with our airplanes, but our fleet can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.56,0:16:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.10,0:16:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Mr. Mitscher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.27,0:16:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you wanna fight a naval battle after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.73,0:16:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? The enemy seems to be headed in the direction of Sasebo, can you catch up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.64,0:16:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we not able to catch up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.60,0:16:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:17:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, Spruance was confused. But he has to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If I miss my chance now, will I be able to meet Yamato again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so, I don't want Yamato to be the prey of airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.78,0:17:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Hello, Ray, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.16,0:17:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to sink the biggest ship in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.30,0:17:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Leave it as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how strong the mark is, it is impossible in today's weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.80,0:17:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds are low and the visibility is 5 or 6 miles. It's impossible to fly. They can't attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The attacks of the 58th, first, 58th, third, fourth, and the MTF will start immediately. {58th here twice?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.80,0:17:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It is 9:40 a.m. now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.40,0:18:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you launch at 10 o'clock, you will be in time for the enemy's lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.00,0:18:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys will be uninvited guests. Then, don't go home until Yamato sinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I say it again. don't come home until Yamato sinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.40,0:19:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,31 knots, Berg and 280 aircraft took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As General Spruance said, the attack wasn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like swimming in a stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Target spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.15,0:19:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A large formation of enemies is approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Man your stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.12,0:19:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,335 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.22,0:19:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Next target, 250, 85 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.79,0:20:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.28,0:22:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I couldn't become a floating battery in Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.08,0:22:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that our decision was not kept secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.87,0:22:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't smoked at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.74,0:22:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I refused to do so until we became floating battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.50,0:22:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you keep your decision secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.98,0:23:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,April 7th, 2:23 p.m. 30 degrees 20 minutes north latitude, 128 degrees 4 minutes east longitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.30,0:23:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato sank in the East China Sea, 200 nautical miles north of Lokunoshima, Kyushu, and 480 meters down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.64,0:23:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Japanese Navy Combined Fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.54,0:23:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which boasted a brilliant tradition since Marshal Togo, has reached its decisive end here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.33,0:23:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese Navy's dominance was swallowed up in the vortex of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.85,0:23:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we can learn how terrifying a blind decision is,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the American side that there must be bold execution after the decision.
